As a translator, I can confirm that the names of cities, especially when they are in a non-Latin script to begin with, usually do not have different translations in different languages. They are generally transliterated into the alphabet of the language, and in this case, all these variants are transliterations of the city name into Latin script. As such, they would remain the same when translated into Italian.
